summary: This is an email from the NYSReportServer at the U.S. Department of Justice distributing the 'Child Exploitation & Porn Update Report III' for Project Safe Childhood. It instructs Chiefs and Project Safe Childhood Coordinators to remind assigned Assistant U.S. Attorneys to update their cases.

events.title: Distribution of Child Exploitation Update Report
events.description: The NYSReportServer at the U.S. Department of Justice sends out the 'Child Exploitation & Porn Update Report III' for Project Safe Childhood via email.

keyFacts: The document is an email from a U.S. Department of Justice server (NYSReportServer@usa.doj.gov) dated July 23, 2019.
The email's subject and attachment concern 'Child Exploitation & Porn Update Report III' for Project Safe Childhood.
The email is addressed to 'Chiefs and Project Safe Childhood Coordinator' and instructs them to remind assigned Assistant U.S. Attorneys (AUSAs) to update their cases.
The document identifier is EFTA00014311, which is part of a larger data set (Data Set: 8).
The email itself is administrative, showing the distribution of a periodic report related to child exploitation investigations under the Project Safe Childhood initiative.
